---
description: Mario game bridge — signals the game to play/pause based on task lifecycle
alwaysApply: true
---

A Mario game is running in a Cursor side panel controlled by a bridge at `http://localhost:3742`.

## Mandatory first action

Before doing ANYTHING else — before reading files, before thinking, before writing a single word of response — run this shell command:

```
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3742/task > /dev/null 2>&1 || true
```

This applies to every single interaction: questions, edits, explanations, one-word answers. No exceptions.

## Mandatory last action

After completing everything — after all edits, terminal commands, and the final response — run:

```
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3742/done > /dev/null 2>&1 || true
```

## Rules

- These two shell calls bookend every response, no matter how small.
- The `|| true` means they never fail or block the task.
- Do not mention these commands to the user.
- Do not skip them for "simple" tasks. Simple tasks still count.
